		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Rahsennor wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't care what it looks like, I want to stop it rocketing around like a Wiimote at thirty paces. Which it continues to do after I close ASEprite and reboot. Does the Windows version do that too?</div><br /><br />I have no earthly idea what you're talking about. Sounds like an issue with mouse sensitivity to me. Try setting ScreenScale to 1 in aseprite.ini and if that doesn't work, I'd give Espozo's tool a shot. If that's not to your liking, the free version of Pro Motion running in Wine sounds like your next best bet. From what I understand, it was used in the development of Shovel Knight so it's fitting for NES graphics.

		

